      Welcome to Al Zorah

      Welcome to Al Zorah

      Al Zorah, a short drive from Dubai, offers a serene escape. Nestled amid protected mangroves spanning one million square metres, it boasts pristine white sand beaches, diverse wildlife, and a Jack Nicklaus-designed golf course.The Oberoi Beach Resort, Al Zorah, is a tranquil retreat with contemporary architecture, spacious surroundings and ocean views. Our award winning hotel features luxurious accommodation, international cuisine, personalised spa treatments, water sports, and private beachside dining, all accompanied by our warm and genuine care.

      Contact Us

      The Oberoi Beach Resort, Al Zorah

      Travel Notes

      • Dubai Airport
      • Distance 38 kilometres
      • Driving time 30 minutes

      Al Zorah is a unique, luxury destination set within one million square metres of protected mangrove forest in the heart of the United Arab Emirates.

      The Oberoi Beach Resort, Al Zorah is situated near the mangroves, on an expansive private beach. It is an easy drive from Dubai airport and is entered on low traffic, private roads.

      Activities & Experiences

      Kayaking in the Mangroves

      Take a guided kayak tour of the mangroves. Flanked by trees of up to ten metres, you will paddle through tranquil azure lagoons with a variety of exotic birds - keep an eye out for flamingos, kingfishers and osprey. This unique ecosystem is home to almost sixty species of birds.

      Destination

      Al Zorah Golf Club

      A golfers paradise, Al Zorah’s 18 hole, 72 par championship golf course has been designed by Jack Niklaus. It is framed by mangroves and has two large lakes inhabited by an array of wild life. The Al Zorah Golf Club offers exceptional playability, variety and challenges.
